criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          1. patients aged 18 to 65 years with active CD, as defined by Harvey-Bradshaw Index (HBI)
             score >4;

          2. patients accompanied with malnutrition as assessed by Nutritional Risk Screening 2002
             (NRS2002) score ≥ 3 or Patient-Generated Subjective Global Assessment (PG-SGA) score ≥
             4;

          3. patients with high compliance.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          1. accompanying with contraindications of enteral nutrition (EN) such as ileus, active
             gastrointestinal bleeding and shock;

          2. severe comorbidities (e.g., Clostridium difficile infection, diabetes, cancer,
             cardiopulmonary failure and severe liver and kidney diseases;

          3. parenteral infection such as urinary infection, pneumonia, etc;

          4. steroids or biologicals use within 6 week;

          5. intestinal fibrotic stenosis;

          6. patients who are pregnant or going to be pregnant;

          7. patients with mental disorders.
